X
1
2
\mathbb{P}(X=1) = \dfrac78
\mathbb{P}(X=2) = \dfrac18
X = \begin{cases} 2 & \text{If the ball removed is }1\\ 1 & \text{else}\end{cases}
\mathbb{E}(X) = \dfrac78 \times 1 + \dfrac18 \times 2 = \dfrac98
Y
7
8
\mathbb{P}(Y=7) = \dfrac18
\mathbb{P}(Y=8) = \dfrac78
Y = \begin{cases} 7 & \text{If the ball removed is }8\\ 8 & \text{else}\end{cases}
\mathbb{E}(Y) = \dfrac78 \times 8 + \dfrac18 \times 7 = \dfrac{63}8
